This paper deals with software analytics and machine learning techniques for defect prediction. The paper discusses the importance of data pre-processing and the use of SMOTUNED, a self-tuning version of SMOTE, to improve the performance of classifiers. This falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also discusses the impact of variations in data on the results, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
